@laurenrosewebb1 yeah I think so, I've had a lot of self consideration as you can probably tell. Does a good job of confusing a person...
Now am I thinking that I have just given up on the questions of my fulfilment, I guess I cant imagine an answer I'll have to find it.
Gone from üò¢>üòê
I guess I cant answer all those questions tonight, but I must keep in mind the balance of doing what is easy and what is right.
Do I want to or would I prefer to suppress those questions and distract myself with the flashy lights of the internet.
So if I am happy overall, why am I not now when I think of my overall life, being a human is complex.
But then I ask my self am I happy, and the answer is yes. I am extremely privileged and can't let myself forget that.
I think I/we get too comfortable in the repetitive nature of our daily lives. I need to look at the bigger picture more often.
I think you need to take the metaphor standing in the past and the future makes you piss on the present, with a pinch of salt.
"The truth resists simplicity"
Turns out the complexity of fulfilling the self goes deep than pineapple and beans
Eating a tin of pineapple and a tin of baked beans, both out of there respective cans, seems to have pulled me out of my unfulfilled mood.
